frameDefinitions: An Agent is described as pursuing an Activity, expending some effort.
This frame covers words for Body_part(s) (BP) belonging to a Possessor (Poss), which may be characterized by a Descriptor (Desc).
This frame is concerned with words that describe a person based on a salient part of their body.
Temporary or permanent Styles and Configurations of Hair, as well as its inherent Nature.
A Protagonist has (or does not have) a Weapon.
This frame covers descriptions of an entire human body, viewed as a gestalt (as opposed to descriptions based on salient body parts).
frameExamples: Sky, a Korean War veteran, was <t>active</t> in his opposition to Vietnam and continues to protest current combat in Iraq.
He had to brace his right <t><fex name='Body_part'>arm</fex></t> against his leg in order to fight the roll.
On either side her head gleamed coiled <t>braids</t> of dark-gold hair , almost pale copper in the subdued light of the room .
Apparently, the suspect is <t>armed</t> with a shotgun.
listRoleDefinitions: This role identifies the name of the ongoing <fen>Activity</fen> in which an <fen>Agent</fen> engages.
The <fen>Agent</fen> engages in an ongoing <fen>Activity</fen>.
An entity acted upon by the <fen>Agent</fen>.
This role identifies the role filled by the <fen>Agent</fen> which is saliently associated with an <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Activity</fen> is pursued.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the  <fen>Activity</fen> is pursued.
This Frame Element denotes the <fen>Possessor</fen> of the <fen>Body_part</fen>.
This Frame Element  is the <fen>Body_part</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Individual</fen> (or individuals) being described.
This role identifies the <fen>Figure</fen> or form being described by the target.
This role is the hair itself
This role is the Possessor of the body part.
Temporary Configurations of hair (eg braid, bun, ponytail).   Something done to the hair merely by movement.
A property of the hair (eg curly, fine, brown).  This acts much like 'Descriptor' in the Observable_bodyparts Frame.  Colors, styles, natural properties are described by this frame element.
The destructive device that the <fen>Protagonist</fen> has with them.
The individual that possesses a <fen>Weapon</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> carries a <fen>Weapon</fen>.
The location where a <fen>Protagonist</fen> carries a <fen>Weapon</fen>.
This role identifies the individual (or individuals) being described.
This role identifies the <fen>Figure</fen> or form being described by the target.
listRoleExamples: He is always active <fex>demolishing the painted figures of men's faith</fex> and then is astonished to find the faith still there clothed in new figure.
<fex>He</fex> was active for six decades as a painter, graphic designer and theorist of art and design.
<fex>As many as 324 companies' stocks</fex> were active across the board.
Jacques Fuller has been active <fex>as a sculptor</fex> in Bloemfontein for almost two decades.
Commercial selling was active <fex>yesterday</fex> but a lack of interest allowed the market to push sharply higher into the mid-session.
He is retired from Whirlpool Corp. in Clyde and is active <fex>at the YMCA</fex>.
The red-haired <fex>figure</fex> stood in the doorway.
